Team Member Role
Primary Responsibilities
Key Deliverables
Member 1: Simulation and Admin
Set up ArduPilot SITL, Ubuntu environment, and pymavlink connection. Build the link-impairment injector to simulate packet loss, delay, jitter, burst dropouts, and full dropouts. Make sure simulation runs are repeatable. Set up a project timeline, coordinate responsibilities, and document progress.
Working SITL simulation environment, MAVLink connection, impairment-injection script, repeatable test scenarios
Member 2: Data and AI Lead
Design and compute link-health features such as heartbeat interval, missed heartbeats, latency, jitter, and dropout streaks to measure signal degradation. Develop the first prediction model, starting with a rule-based risk score and then possibly a lightweight classifier (depending on difficulty and time).
Feature definitions, telemetry logging pipeline, labeled dataset, risk model, predicted loss score output
Member 3: Controls and Recovery Lead
Design and implement the intervention state machine. Map risk levels to actions such as climb, slow down, loiter, return-to-home, or return-to-last-good-link. Add hysteresis and dwell time to prevent unstable switching. If this proves to be time consuming, warnings or classifications of expected interferences can be made.
Intervention logic, state machine, prevention/recovery behaviors, simulator-integrated control actions
Member 4: Evaluation and Presentation Lead
Design the experiment plan comparing baseline flights and AI-enabled flights. Track metrics such as battery usage, time without link, recovery time, and mission disruption. Create graphs, visuals, slides, and coordinate the final report and presentation.
Experiment matrix, evaluation metrics, charts/graphs, presentation visuals, final report coordination




